        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 4 at 1:50PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 148 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking an outflow boundary ahead
of a line of storms extending from near Dinero to near Port Aransas.
Movement was southwest at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Corpus Christi, Portland, Robstown, Sinton, Mathis, Port Aransas,
Taft, Corpus Christi International Airport, Ingleside, Odem, Gregory,
Orange Grove, Ingleside On The Bay, Lake City, San Patricio, Midway,
Corpus Christi North Beach, Kings Crossing Subdivision, Bay Area
Medical Center, and Spohn Hospital South.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 37 between mile markers 1 and 47.
US Highway 281 between mile markers 646 and 658.
US Highway 181 between mile markers 638 and 648.
US Highway 77 between mile markers 648 and 672.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
